race.comment: ROCK THE MARKET (9) broke through for a well-deserved first win last start over 1200m at Ascot, getting home by a long neck. She has plenty of scope, and in a field that is not much harder, she can take the next step immediately. BACKCHATTING (3) franked a solid trial win when scoring fresh up over 1300m here last start, and he looks a lot stronger this season as a 3-year-old. He is well placed to win again. PYGMALION (8) was out of the money two runs ago, then finished fourth, two lengths away, over 1100m at Bunbury last time out. The winkers are on, and he has each-way claims again. MAVIS MYRTLE (11) drops in grade after finishing well back over 1200m at Ascot 11 days ago. She could bounce back in form at good odds here. Don't risk her. COME ON EMMA (4) resumed with a narrow third at Ascot and will continue to improve with racing. Stick with her.
